From: chat-template-patches
Subject: [Q3.6-4] Tool-call string-argument passthrough (R2 port)

Targets: templates/qwen3.6/patched/35B-A3B.jinja (state after Q3.6-1 + Q3.6-2 + Q3.6-3 applied)

OpenAI-compat clients (Codex, OpenWebUI, mlx-lm server in some configs) send
`tool_calls[*].function.arguments` as a JSON-encoded STRING rather than the
mapping form Qwen3.6's template assumes. The upstream `is mapping` guard
silently drops the entire parameter body — the rendered tool call has
`<function=NAME>` immediately followed by `</function>` with no payload, so
the model has no record of the arguments it allegedly used.

Fix: add an `elif tool_call.arguments is string` branch that emits the
trimmed string verbatim (with trailing newline). Mapping arguments still
take the original `<parameter=...>` per-key path. Bare string-form arguments
are emitted as a single block, which downstream parsers expecting JSON can
parse from `<function=...>` … `</function>` directly.

Sibling: R2 in the Qwen3.5 catalog (barubary's Fix 9). Cross-confirmed by
froggeric's r/LocalLLaMA `1sdhvc5` thread and ml-explore/mlx-lm#1065.

Stacks on Q3.6-1 + Q3.6-2 + Q3.6-3. Diff is against the Q3.6-3-applied state.

--- a/templates/qwen3.6/patched/35B-A3B.jinja
+++ b/templates/qwen3.6/patched/35B-A3B.jinja
@@ -134,6 +134,11 @@
                         {{- args_value }}
                         {{- '\n</parameter>\n' }}
                     {%- endfor %}
+                {%- elif tool_call.arguments is string %}
+                    {%- if tool_call.arguments|trim %}
+                        {{- tool_call.arguments }}
+                        {{- '\n' }}
+                    {%- endif %}
                 {%- endif %}
                 {{- '</function>\n</tool_call>' }}
             {%- endfor %}
